      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The nested loop is O(n²), which will fail for n=10⁷. I can optimize this to O(n) by precomputing the sum of integers and using the formula for the sum of products. Here is the optimized code:\n\n```python\ndef solve_sequence(n):\n    if n == 0: return 0\n    total_sum = n * (n + 1) // 2\n    result = 0\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\n        result += (i * total_sum) % 123\n    return result\n```\n\nThis reduces the complexity from quadratic to linear, ensuring it runs fast enough for large inputs.",
